snippet.textDisplay: Anyone else slightly blown away by the fact that that GaN USB-C/HDMI brick wasn't kickstarted by Anker? Also, I haven't ever seen a charging brick with USB-C, USB-A, and HDMI all together. I'm surprised that Human Things is leaning so far into their "premium Nintendo Switch accessories company" branding that their materials talking about more general purpose applications is kinda an afterthought buried under Switch-oriented promotional information. It's like they're just talking straight past the rest of the market that might be interested in a GaN charging brick that has built-in HDMI output. I'm a bit disappointed that TechLinked didn't bring up the other potential applications of this.
snippet.textOriginal: Anyone else slightly blown away by the fact that that GaN USB-C/HDMI brick wasn't kickstarted by Anker?
